quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  93,1,"By the morning shine."
  93,2,"By the night as it settles—"
  93,3,"your Lord has not abandoned yousg , nor has He despised(you) ."
  93,4,"And indeed the Last is better for yousg than the First,"
  93,5,"and your Lord will certainly give you so that you will be well pleased."
  93,6,"Did He not find yousg an orphan, so He sheltered(you) ;"
  93,7,"and found you wandering, so He guided(you) ;"
  93,8,"and found you in need, so He enriched(you) ?"
  93,9,"So as for the orphan, dosg not subdue;"
  93,10,"and as for the asker, do not rebuke;"
  94,1,"Did We not expand yoursg chest,"
  94,2,"and lift from you your burden"
  94,3,"which weighed down your back,"
  94,4,"and raised for you your remembrance1?"
  94,5,"So indeed, with hardship comes ease;"
  94,6,"indeed, with hardship comes ease."
  94,7,"So whenever yousg are done(from work) , stand up1,"
  94,8,"and to your Lord turn wishfully."